<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-375-452  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 375 452.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>MacUser  June 1990 v6 n6 p46(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT Ziff-Davis Publishing Co. 1990.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>WriteImpact. (Hardware Review) (GCC Technologies WriteImpact24-pin dot matrix printer)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Wiggins, Robert R.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   GCC Technologies Inc. (products).andO;Product:   GCC Technologies WriteImpact (Computer printer) (evaluation).andO;Topic:     Dot-Matrix PrintersEvaluation.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>WriteImpactandM;Advanced highquality printers can't do multipart forms.andP;  For such forms, youstill need an impact printer.andM;The WriteImpact is GCC's entry in the near-letter-quality impact-printermarket, and it's not bad.andP;  It's excellent at paper handling, offering bothpush and pull tractor feed as well as friction feed.andP;  Print quality is good.andM;The WriteImpact comes with its own Chooser-level printer driver that supportsits special features, such as font smoothing, bit-map smoothing, scaling (25to 400 percent), print preview, and kerning.andP;  You also get Quick-Spool II (abackground spooler) and GCC's Print Manager for dealing with the batch-modeprint queue.andP;  The WriteImpact uses special Bitstream fonts to achieve itshigh quality.andP;  They take up disk space (about 65K per font and style), andnot every popular screen font has a corresponding Bitstream font.andO;Fortunately, the WriteImpact works fine with Adobe Type Manager, which makesall the Adobe fonts usable.andM;The WriteImpact is a good value for the money.andP;  You get ImageWriter LQquality at an ImageWriter price (and without the problems of the LQ).andP;  TheWriteImpact's only major drawback is that it's a serial device with nonetworkable AppleTalk version.andO;</TEXT></DOC>